nt|^b@2^z@3Now let's take a look at the other side of the coin. Assume that West chooses hearts for his opening lead against a notrump contract. West has only 3 cards in hearts and since every bridge hand contains at least one suit with at least 4 cards, hearts cannot be West's longest suit. Perhaps the opponents have bid West's longest suit and, among the unbid suits, West's heart holding looks to be the most promising.|
