There are some holdings that are headed by the Ace-King where the Ace could be right to lead against a notrump contract. 

Other times the opening leader will do better to lead either the King (asking for an attitude signal) or the 4th best card from these holdings. Here are some examples of such holdings:^^

|
pg| ***** 131 ***** |


cs|3|at|^B  { |ih|psakj72|at|} |n#|g|at|^H  { |ih|phakt95|at|} |n^|r|at|^N  { |ih|pcakj7|at|} |n#|e|at|^T  { |ih|pdakt643|at|} |n^|z|at|

Each of the above are very powerful holdings headed by the Ace-King, but there is more than one honor card missing in each case. 

The question as to whether you should lead the Ace (asking partner to drop an honor or give count), the King (asking for an attitude signal), or the 4th best card from these holdings is not an easy one to answer. 

Any of the options could work out best for the holdings on a given deal. These are judgment calls.

|
